description: Uploads a batch of log events to the specified log stream. The batch of events must satisfy the following constraints: If a call to PutLogEvents returns 'UnrecognizedClientException' the most likely cause is a non-valid Amazon Web Services access key ID or secret key.

parameters.name: logGroupName
parameters.description: The name of the log group.

parameters.name: logStreamName
parameters.description: The name of the log stream.

parameters.name: logEvents
parameters.description: The log events. (dict) --- Represents a log event, which is a record of activity that was recorded by the application or resource being monitored. The time the event occurred, expressed as the number of milliseconds after Jan 1, 1970 00:00:00 UTC. The raw event message. Each log event can be no larger than 1 MB.

nested_params.name: timestamp
nested_params.description: The time the event occurred, expressed as the number of milliseconds after Jan 1, 1970 00:00:00 UTC.

nested_params.name: message
nested_params.description: The raw event message. Each log event can be no larger than 1 MB.

parameters.name: sequenceToken
parameters.description: The sequence token obtained from the response of the previous PutLogEvents call.

parameters.name: entity
parameters.description: The entity associated with the log events. keyAttributes (dict) --- The attributes of the entity which identify the specific entity, as a list of key-value pairs. Entities with the same keyAttributes are considered to be the same entity. There are five allowed attributes (key names): Type, ResourceType, Identifier Name, and Environment. For details about how to use the key attributes, see How to add related information to telemetry in the CloudWatch User Guide. (string) --- (string) --- attributes (dict) --- Additional attributes of the entity that are not used to specify the identity of the entity. A list of key-value pairs. For details about how to use the attributes, see How to add related information to telemetry in the CloudWatch User Guide. (string) --- (string) ---

nested_params.name: keyAttributes
nested_params.description: The attributes of the entity which identify the specific entity, as a list of key-value pairs. Entities with the same keyAttributes are considered to be the same entity. There are five allowed attributes (key names): Type, ResourceType, Identifier Name, and Environment. For details about how to use the key attributes, see How to add related information to telemetry in the CloudWatch User Guide.

nested_params.name: attributes
nested_params.description: Additional attributes of the entity that are not used to specify the identity of the entity. A list of key-value pairs. For details about how to use the attributes, see How to add related information to telemetry in the CloudWatch User Guide.

nested_items.name: tooNewLogEventStartIndex
nested_items.description: The index of the first log event that is too new. This field is inclusive.

nested_items.name: tooOldLogEventEndIndex
nested_items.description: The index of the last log event that is too old. This field is exclusive.

nested_items.name: rejectedEntityInfo
nested_items.description: Information about why the entity is rejected when calling PutLogEvents. Only returned when the entity is rejected.

nested_items.name: errorType
nested_items.description: The type of error that caused the rejection of the entity when calling PutLogEvents.
